* {{audio|en-us-sit.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪt}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|sits|sitting|'''[[sat]]''' or '''[[sate]]'''<ref>[http://machaut.uchicago.edu/?action=search&word=sate&resource=Webster%27s&quicksearch=on Entry] about past simple sate in Webster's dictionary</ref>|'''[[sat]]''' or rarely '''[[sitten]]'''}}

# {{context|intransitive|of a person}} To be in a position in which the upper body is upright and the [[leg]]s (especially the upper legs) are supported by some object.
#: ''After a long day of walking, it was good just to '''sit''' and relax.''
# {{context|intransitive|of a person}} To move oneself into such a position.
#: ''I asked him to '''sit'''.''
# {{context|intransitive|of an object}} To occupy a given position permanently.
#: ''The temple has '''sat''' atop that hill for centuries.''
# To be a member of a [[deliberative]] body.
#: ''I currently '''sit''' on a standards committee.''
# {{context|intransitive|of an agreement or arrangement}} To be accepted.
#: ''How will this new contract '''sit''' with the workers?''
#: ''I don’t think it will '''sit''' well.''
# {{law|government}} Of a legislative or, especially, a judicial body such as a court, to be in [[session]].
#: ''In what city is the circuit court '''sitting''' for this session.''

